  "prompt": "Why do guys stare at girls then look away?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why someone might stare and then quickly look away:\n\n1. Attraction\n- Finding the person physically attractive\n- Being interested but feeling shy or nervous\n- Wanting to look but not wanting to seem obvious\n\n2. Social Awkwardness\n- Lack of social confidence\n- Not knowing how to interact appropriately\n- Feeling uncomfortable with direct eye contact\n\n3. Curiosity\n- Something about the person catches their attention\n- Wondering about something specific about the person\n\n4. Psychological Reasons\n- Unconscious behavior\n- Not realizing they're staring\n- Unintentional glance\n\n5. Cultural or Personal Factors\n- Different comfort levels with eye contact\n- Personal background or upbringing\n- Individual personality traits\n\n6. Potential Negative Reasons\n- Inappropriate intentions\n- Judging or evaluating\n- Feeling critical\n\nThe specific reason varies depending on the individual and the context. Not all staring indicates the same motivation.\n\nIf someone's staring makes you uncomfortable, it's okay to:\n- Look directly at them\n- Move away\n- Address the behavior if you feel safe doing so",
